title: Cheesy Sloppy Joe Bake Jamie Sherman
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray an 8x8-inch or 9x9-inch square baking dish with PAM cooking spray and set aside.
Brown and crumble ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain, if necessary. Stir in the MANWICH. Spread beef mixture into the prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle the cheese over the top.
In small bowl, stir together the pancake and baking mix, milk, and eggs with fork or wire whisk until blended. Pour over the cheese.
Bake about 25-30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
ingredients: 1-1½ lb. lean ground beef or ground turkey
1 can (15 oz.) MANWICH Original Sloppy Joe Sauce
½ cup pancake and baking mix
